#•	User Subscription Service:
A Python-based REST API (using Flask or FastAPI) that handles user registration, preference management, and unsubscriptions.
•	Database:
Use Cloud Firestore (for document-based storage) or Cloud SQL (for relational data) to store user profiles.
•	API Gateway:
Manage and secure your APIs with Cloud Endpoints.
•	Messaging Layer:
Google Cloud Pub/Sub can asynchronously send notifications or trigger workflows in the Weather API Service.
•	Deployment & Orchestration:
Containerize your Python service with Docker and deploy on Cloud Run for a serverless experience—or use GKE for more control if needed.
•	Monitoring & Security:
Integrate Cloud Monitoring and Logging for real-time insights and use Firebase Auth or OAuth for securing endpoints.
